==English==
===Etymology===
Ecclesiastical Latin [[homoeusius]], from Greek [[ὁμοιουσιος]], from [[ὁμοιος]] ‘like, similar’ + [[ουσια]] ‘essence’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/hɒmɔɪ'u:zɪən/}}

===Adjective===
{{en-ad|homoiousian}}
# having a similar but not identical [[essence]], especially with reference to the first and second persons of the [[Trinity]]

